# Model Conventions

## Model Inventory (10 models)

| Model | Parent | Key Fields | Ordering |
|-------|--------|-----------|----------|
| Subject | — | slug (unique), name, description, accent_color, order | order |
| Chapter | Subject FK | chapter_number, part, title, subtitle, order | order, chapter_number |
| Question | Chapter FK | order, question, difficulty, tldr, answer, points (JSON), diagram, diagram2, table_data (JSON), followup | order |
| Takeaway | Chapter FK | order, content | order |
| Highlight | User FK + Chapter FK | question_index, text, color, created_at | -created_at |
| Note | User FK | subject FK?, chapter FK?, content, ai_summary | -updated_at |
| StagedRequest | User FK | operation, target_model, target_id?, payload (JSON), status, review_note | -created_at |
| Subscription | Subject FK | email, user FK?, difficulty, custom_prompt, is_active, last_sent_at | -created_at |
| EmailTopic | Subject FK | title, keywords (JSON), source, chapter FK?, is_active | subject, title |
| SentHistory | Subscription FK + Topic FK | sent_at, questions_json (JSON) | -sent_at |

## StagedRequest

- `operation`: create | update | delete
- `target_model`: subject | chapter | question | takeaway | chapter_populate
- `chapter_populate`: payload = `{chapter_title, questions: [...], takeaways: [...]}`
- `apply(reviewer)`: for standard models, creates/updates/deletes directly; for `chapter_populate`, calls `_apply_chapter_populate()` which atomically replaces all questions + takeaways
- `reject(reviewer, note)`: sets status=rejected

## Rules

- snake_case fields; ForeignKey named by related model
- JSONField: `default=list` or `default=dict`, not `null=True`
- Every model: `Meta.ordering`, meaningful `__str__`
- User-scoped models always filter by `user=request.user` in views
- Run `makemigrations` after every model change

## Admin

- Every model registered in `admin.py` (except EmailTopic, SentHistory)
- StagedRequest admin: styled HTML preview, default pending filter, bulk approve/reject
- Subscription admin: send test DeltaMail action
- Chapter admin: inline Questions + Takeaways, preview link
